The paper proposes distributed algorithms for multi-agent networks, which suggests that it may belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) category. The focus on linear equations and optimization suggests that it may also belong to the Mathematical Optimization (cs.MA) and Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) categories. The use of numerical simulations suggests that it may belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) categories.
